Data Collection Method: Jamar Count Board
1) Fantasy World Academy Preschool, Preschool Connection,
Catawba Heights Elementary School, & Belmont Abbey
College are located less than one mile from the studied
intersection and were in session on the date of the count,
as were all Gaston County Schools.
2) Pedestrians were observed and counted – none were
3) SB approach grade is +1% and NB, EB, & WB are -1%.
4) Area lighting was present at the count location.
5) No highway construction was observed that impacted normal traffic patterns.
6) Data collection equipment was operating correctly at time of count.
7) Counters took breaks from 9:00 – 9:15 AM and 3:00 – 3:30 PM. Data for these periods was interpolated.
8) Counter Notes: The EB rights in the count report represent the vehicles that traveled east on Ferstl Avenue
and made a 90° right on Beaty Road. The vehicles that made a right off of Ferstl Avenue onto the ramp prior
to the study area intersection were counted separately on Bank 2 of the count board.
